"Also, Stats signals were renamed and now pass around spider references "
"(instead of domains). Here's a summary of the changes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:820
msgid ""
"To quickly port your code (to work with Scrapy 0.8) just use ``spider."
"domain_name`` where you previously used ``domain``. ``spider_stats`` "
"contains exactly the same data as ``domain_stats``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:823
msgid ""
"``CloseDomain`` extension moved to ``scrapy.contrib.closespider."
"CloseSpider`` (:rev:`1833`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:823
msgid "Its settings were also renamed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:823
msgid "``CLOSEDOMAIN_TIMEOUT`` to ``CLOSESPIDER_TIMEOUT``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:824
msgid "``CLOSEDOMAIN_ITEMCOUNT`` to ``CLOSESPIDER_ITEMCOUNT``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:825
msgid ""
"Removed deprecated ``SCRAPYSETTINGS_MODULE`` environment variable - use "
"``SCRAPY_SETTINGS_MODULE`` instead (:rev:`1840`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:826
msgid ""
"Renamed setting: ``REQUESTS_PER_DOMAIN`` to "
"``CONCURRENT_REQUESTS_PER_SPIDER`` (:rev:`1830`, :rev:`1844`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:827
msgid ""
"Renamed setting: ``CONCURRENT_DOMAINS`` to ``CONCURRENT_SPIDERS`` (:rev:"
"`1830`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:828
msgid "Refactored HTTP Cache middleware"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:829
msgid ""
"HTTP Cache middleware has been heavilty refactored, retaining the same "
"functionality except for the domain sectorization which was removed. (:rev:"
"`1843` )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:830
msgid ""
"Renamed exception: ``DontCloseDomain`` to ``DontCloseSpider`` (:rev:`1859` | "
"#120)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../news.rst:831
msgid ""
"Renamed extension: ``DelayedCloseDomain`` to ``SpiderCloseDelay`` (:rev:"
"`1861` | #121)"
msgstr ""

